data.chText: 缓慢移动；发展缓慢；滞后；落后于
data.enText: to move or develop slowly or more slowly than other people, organizations, etc.

data.chText: 那小男孩落在了父母的后面。
data.enText: The little boy lagged behind his parents.

data.chText: 我们在运用现代技术方面仍然远远落后于我们的许多竞争对手。
data.enText: We still lag far behind many of our competitors in using modern technology.

data.chText: 给（管道等）加防冻保暖层
data.enText: to cover pipes, etc. with a special material to stop the water in them from freezing, or to save heat

means: 给(管道等)加防冻保暖层

tr: the act of slowing down or falling behind
one of several thin slats of wood forming the sides of a barrel or bucket
the time between one event, process, or period and another
example: meanwhile the socialists are running the government

tr: cover with lagging to prevent heat loss
throw or pitch at a mark, as with coins
hang (back) or fall (behind) in movement, progress, development, etc.
lock up or confine, in or as in a jail
example: The suspects were imprisoned without trial
the murderer was incarcerated for the rest of his life

value.def: If one thing or person lags behind another thing or person, their progress is slower than that of the other.

example.ex: Britain still lags behind most of Europe in its provisions for women who want time off to have babies...
example.tran: 英国在妇女生育福利方面依然落后于欧洲大多数国家。

example.ex: The restructuring of the pattern of consumption in Britain also lagged behind...
example.tran: 在消费结构重组方面，英国也落后于人。

example.ex: He now lags 10 points behind the champion...
A poll for the Observer showed Labour on 39 per cent with the Tories lagging a point behind...
example.tran: 《观察家报》一项民意调查显示，工党支持率为39%，保守党落后其1个百分点。

example.ex: Hague was lagging badly in the polls.
example.tran: 黑格在民意调查中被远远抛在后面。

value.def: A time lag or a lag of a particular length of time is a period of time between one event and another related event.

example.ex: There's  a time lag between infection with HIV and developing AIDS...
example.tran: 从感染艾滋病病毒到病发有一段滞后期。

example.ex: Price rises have matched rises in the money supply with a lag of two or three months.
example.tran: 在增加货币供应两三个月后，物价也跟着上涨。

value.def: If you lag the inside of a roof, a pipe, or a water tank, you cover it with a special material in order to prevent heat escaping from it or to prevent it from freezing.

example.ex: If you have to take the floorboards up, take the opportunity to lag any pipes at the same time...
example.tran: 如果一定要把地板掀开，不妨趁此机会给各个管道加一层隔热保护。

example.ex: Water tanks should be well lagged and the roof well insulated.
example.tran: 水箱和屋顶都需要敷设严密的保温层。

value.tran: 给（屋顶、水管或水箱）装绝热层

trans: (两件相关事件的)时间间隔，时滞
